\i Ship/Captain/Crew (654):
\i0 \
A player has up to three throws. The first six (Ship) then five (captain) and then four (crew) are set aside when they are thrown. The sum of the remaining two dice is the result. The player with the highest (or lowest) score wins. If 6, 5 and 4 where not achieved after three throws, there is no score (bust). We will select the dice that can be thrown so a simple tap/swipe is sufficient.\
